'''BritBangla''' ({{lang-bn|<U+09AC><U+09CD><U+09B0><U+09BF><U+099F><U+09BF> <U+09AC><U+09BE><U+0982><U+09B2><U+09BE><U+0964>}}) is a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Social networking service|social]] and [[Professional network service|professional networking association]] to highlight and promote the work, achievements and contributions of British [[Bengali people|Bengalis]]. The association was founded in 2003 and is based in [[London]], [[England]].

==History==
BritBangla was founded by [[Taryn Khanam]] and Shirin Hussain.<ref name="manchestereveningnews">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/news/local-news/bengali-women-past-and-present-celebrated-885308|title=Bengali women past and present celebrated|work= |location=Manchester|publisher=''[[Manchester Evening News]]''|date=15 March 2010|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> On 12 April 2003, the association was launched in [[Alexandra Palace]], [[London]].<ref name="asiancommunity">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.asiancommunity.net/bangladesh_Brit_Bangla.htm|title=British Bengalis launch "BritBangla"|work= |location= |publisher=''Asian community''|date=12 April 2003|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref>

On 28 February 2010, the association held a network launch event for the West Midlands in [[Birmingham]], its first outside London.<ref name="marketingbirmingham">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.marketingbirmingham.com/media_office/city_news/2/2010/1263/bengali_networking_comes_to_birmingham/|title=Bengali networking comes to Birmingham|work= |location=Birmingham|publisher=''Marketing Birmingham''|date=February 2010|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref>

In October 2011, the association held an event hosted by [[Nazir Ahmed, Baron Ahmed|Lord Nazir Ahmed]] at the [[House of Lords]], it was organised in conjunction with the [[Embassy of the United States, London|U.S. Embassy in London]] and The Concordia Forum. It brought together members of the UK and U.S. Muslim communities in order to provide a platform for establishing bilateral links and facilitate networking.<ref name="asianimage">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/9314522.US_Special_Envoy_attends_House_of_Lords_talk/|title=US Special Envoy attends House of Lords talk|work= |location= |publisher=''Asian Image''|date=20 October 2010|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> 

==Aim==
BritBangla is a national networking association<ref name="marketingbirmingham"/> that brings together second and third generation<ref name="alalodulal">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.alalodulal.org/2012/12/19/british/|title=British Bangladeshi <U+201C>Power 100<U+2033>|work= |location= |publisher=''Alal O Dulal''|date=19 December 2012|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> Bengali professionals in the United Kingdom<ref name="redhotcurry">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.redhotcurry.com/news/2011/brit-bangla.htm|title=BritBangla hosts the U.S. Special Envoy for Islamic Cooperation|work= |location= |publisher=''Redhotcurry.com''|date=17 November 2011|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> to serve to the local and international community<ref name="asianimage">{{cite news |last= |first= |url=http://www.asianimage.co.uk/news/9314522.US_Special_Envoy_attends_House_of_Lords_talk/|title=US Special Envoy attends House of Lords talk|work= |location= |publisher=''Asian Image''|date=20 October 2010|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> and has built a reputation for its social, cultural, careers and networking events.<ref name="alalodulal"/>

The association has more than 1,000 members<ref name="marketingbirmingham"/> from business, media, teaching, finance and the public sector. It provides a platform for [[Bengali people]] to voice their views and aspirations,<ref name="bbwhoswho09">{{cite book |last1=Karim|first1=Mohammed Abdul|last2=Karim|first2=Shahadoth|title=British Bangladeshi Who's Who|url=http://www.bbwhoswho.co.uk/whoswho_09.pdf|date=October 2009|publisher=British Bangla Media Group|page=|isbn= |accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> by bringing together like-minded people through social and charitable events, workshops, seminars, undertaking fundraising activities for charities, providing community support,<ref name="britbangla">{{cite web |url=http://www.britbangla.net/aboutus.html|title=About Us|publisher=BritBangla|date=November 2012|accessdate=1 November 2014}}</ref> providing a network, and promoting the talents, achievements<ref name="marketingbirmingham"/> and contribution<ref name="alalodulal"/> of British<ref name="marketingbirmingham"/> professionals of Bengali descent (from Bangladesh and India).<ref name="manchestereveningnews"/>

The association is for all [[Bengali language|Bengali]]-speaking people, is also all-inclusive and welcomes anyone with an interest in the Bengali community who wants to join regardless of race or religious background.<ref name="marketingbirmingham"/> It has also received air time from media organisations including, [[BBC]] and [[Channel 4]].<ref name="bbwhoswho09"/>

